13/03/2005
THE HAGUE, Netherlands -- Former Kosovo Prime Minister Ramush Haradinaj is expected to make his first appearance before the UN war crimes tribunal at The Hague on Monday (14 March). He is to appear before the judges together with two fellow former Kosovo Albanian guerrillas, Idriz Balaj and Lah Brahimaj, whose names are on the same indictment for crimes committed against Serb and non-Albanian civilians in Kosovo in 1998. 
Also Friday, there was an explosion just outside the UN compound in Pristina. The suspected hand grenade injured at least one person. (RTRS - 13/03/05; Kathimerini - 12/03/05; Tanjug, KosovaLive BBC, AFP, AP - 11/03/05) 
